00001 /*****************************************************************************
00002  
00003   Module:  odldef.h
00004 
00005   Description:  This C-language include file contains declarations for
00006                 data structures used by PDS Object Description Language
00007                 (ODL) processing software.  No storage is allocated.
00008  
00009   Author:  Randy Davis, University of Colorado LASP
00010  
00011   Creation Date: 12 March 1989
00012   Last Modified: 18 May 1991
00013 
00014   History:
00015 
00016   Creation - This include file was included in the Version 1 release of
00017   the ODLC library.
00018 
00019   Version 2.0 - 30 August 1990 - R. Davis, U. of Colorado LASP
00020     a) Data structures and function prototypes have been modified to support
00021        ODL Version 2. The biggest change is that the Object_Node data
00022        structure has been supplanted by an Aggregate_Node that handles
00023        groups as well as objects, and the Attribute_Node structure by a
00024        Parameter_Node structure for both attributes and pointers.
00025   
00026   Version 2.1 - 13 March 1991 - R. Davis, U. of Colorado LASP
00027     a) Added support for comments for aggregate and parameter nodes.  Also
00028        added two fields to aggregates node for use by end-user applications.
00029     b) Eliminated the level field for aggregate structures.
00030 
00031   Version 2.2 - 18 May 1991- M. DeMore, Jet Propulsion Laboratory
00032     a) Added two fields to the parameter node for use by the PDS toolbox.
00033     b) Reorganized and added prototypes to create generic version for both
00034        Unix and VMS
00035 Ocy. 18, 1999   Abe Taaheri Changed ODLMAXSTMT value from 24000 to 255001 to
00036                             make it consistent with the max lengthes set in the
00037                 MET header files for array length and each array
00038                 element length, i.e. 1000 and 255 
00039                 (per NCR ECSed24377)
00040 *****************************************************************************/

00105 /* The following structure contains information about a single object or
00106    group including its name and (for objects) its class.  The structure
00107    contains pointers that thread the object/group nodes together and that
00108    connect an object or group with attributes.  */
00109 
00110 struct Aggregate_Node
00111 {
00112    char                  *name;            /* Name of the object or group   */
00113    char                  *objClass;        /* The class of object           */
00114    char                  *comment;         /* Annotation                    */
00115    AGGREGATE_KIND         kind;            /* Kind of node (object or group)*/
00116    long                   appl1;           /* Available for application use */
00117    long                   appl2;           /* Available for application use */
00118    struct Aggregate_Node *parent;          /* Pointer to parent node        */
00119    struct Aggregate_Node *left_sibling;    /* Pointer to sibling on left    */
00120    struct Aggregate_Node *right_sibling;   /* Pointer to sibling on right   */
00121    struct Aggregate_Node *first_child;     /* Pointer to first child        */
00122    struct Aggregate_Node *last_child;      /* Pointer to last child         */
00123    struct Parameter_Node *first_parameter; /* Pointer to first parameter    */
00124    struct Parameter_Node *last_parameter;  /* Pointer to last parameter     */
00125 };
00126 
00127 /* The following structure contains information about a parameter -- an
00128    attribute of an object or a pointer.  This includes the attribute or
00129    pointer name and the kind of value associated with the parameter
00130    (scalar, sequence or set).  For sequences the number of rows and
00131    columns are given.  Each parameter node contains a pointer to the 
00132    aggregate -- group or object -- node to which it belongs and a list
00133    of values associated with the parameter.  All of the parameter nodes
00134    for an aggregat are threaded together in a doubly-linked list.  */
00135 
00136 struct Parameter_Node
00137 {
00138    char                  *name;           /* The name of the parameter      */
00139    char                  *comment;        /* Annotation                     */
00140    PARAMETER_KIND         node_kind;      /* Param kind (Attribute or Ptr)  */
00141    VALUE_KIND             value_kind;     /* Indicates the kind of value    */
00142    long                   value_count;    /* Total number of values         */
00143    short                  columns;        /* Number of columns in sequence  */
00144    short                  rows;           /* Number of rows in sequence     */
00145    struct Aggregate_Node *owner;          /* Pointer to parameter's owner   */
00146    struct Parameter_Node *left_sibling;   /* Pointer to parameter to left   */
00147    struct Parameter_Node *right_sibling;  /* Pointer to parameter to right  */
00148    struct Value_Node     *first_value;    /* Pointer to first value node    */
00149    struct Value_Node     *last_value;     /* Pointer to last value node     */
00150 
00151 /* >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> BEGIN CN CHANGES >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> */
00152 /* >>>>> MDD 5/14/91  Added the appl1 and appl2 fields to the      >>>>> */
00153 /* >>>>>              parameter structure                          >>>>> */
00154 /* >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> */
00155 
00156 #ifdef PDS_TOOLBOX
00157 
00158   long appl1;                              /* Application defined field 1    */
00159   long appl2;                              /* Application defined field 2    */
00160 
00161 #endif
00162 
00163 /* >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> END OF CN CHANGES >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> */
00164 
00165 };
00166 
00167 /* The following structures are used to hold information on a single value.
00168    The ODLReal structure holds a double precision floating point value
00169    and a pointer to a (possibly null) list of units designators which
00170    are represented through the ODLUnits structure.  Similarly, the
00171    ODLInteger structure holds a long integer value and units. The
00172    ODLDate structure holds date and time values.                            */
00173 
00174 struct ODLUnits
00175 {
00176   char             *designator;           /* Pointer to name of units       */
00177   long              exponent;             /* Exponent for units             */
00178   struct ODLUnits  *next_field;           /* Pointer to next units          */
00179 };
00180 
00181 
00182 struct ODLReal
00183 {
00184   double            number;               /* The floating numeric value     */
00185   struct ODLUnits  *units;                /* Pointer to units list          */
00186 };
00187 
00188 
00189 struct ODLInteger
00190 {
00191   long              number;               /* The integer numeric value      */
00192   struct ODLUnits  *units;                /* Pointer to units list          */
00193 };
00194 
00195 
00196 struct ODLDate
00197 {
00198   short             year;                 /* Year number                    */
00199   short             doy;                  /* Day of year (0-366)            */
00200   char              month;                /* Month of year (1-12)           */
00201   char              day;                  /* Day of month (1-31)            */
00202   short             zone_hours;           /* Zone hours from GMT (-12 - +12)*/
00203   char              zone_minutes;         /* Zone minutes from GMT (0-59)   */
00204   char              hours;                /* Hours of day (0-23)            */
00205   char              minutes;              /* Minutes of hour (0-59)         */
00206   char              seconds;              /* Seconds of minute (0-59)       */
00207   long              nanoseconds;          /* Nanoseconds (0-999999999)      */
00208 };
00209 
00210 
00211 struct Value_Data
00212 {
00213    VALUE_TYPE                 type;       /* Indicator of value type        */
00214    char                       valid;      /* Value valid if this is > 0     */
00215    char                       format;     /* Value-specific format indicator*/
00216    short                      precision;  /* Value-specific precision       */
00217    short                      length;     /* Number of chars in value field */
00218    union {
00219             struct ODLInteger integer;    /* Integer value                  */
00220             struct ODLReal    real;       /* Real value                     */
00221             struct ODLDate    date_time;  /* Date and time value            */
00222             char             *string;     /* Pointer to text value          */
00223          } value;
00224 };
00225 
00226 
00227 struct Value_Node
00228 {
00229    struct Value_Data      item;           /* Data value                     */
00230    struct Parameter_Node *parameter;      /* Pointer to value's parameter   */
00231    struct Value_Node     *left_sibling;   /* Pointer to value to left       */
00232    struct Value_Node     *right_sibling;  /* Pointer to value to right      */
00233 };

00239 /* Because object, group, attribute and value nodes are created in virtual
00240    memory, they are almost always referred to using pointers. The following
00241    types are therefore defined to be equivalent to pointers to the
00242    aggregate, parameter and value structures */
00243 
00244 typedef struct Aggregate_Node *AGGREGATE;
00245 typedef struct Aggregate_Node *OBJECT;
00246 typedef struct Aggregate_Node *GROUP;
00247 
00248 typedef struct Parameter_Node *PARAMETER;
00249 typedef struct Parameter_Node *ATTRIBUTE;
00250 typedef struct Parameter_Node *POINTER;
00251 
00252 typedef struct Value_Node     *VALUE;
00253 
00254 /* The following provides an alternative name for the often-used structure
00255    that is used to hold a data value.                                       */
00256 
00257 typedef struct Value_Data      VALUE_DATA;
